  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nRight now for each epoch, we have 3 or 4 or 5 epoch transitions\r\n\r\n<img width=\"807\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2021-10-01 at 17 22 08\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10568965/135605003-4792e687-01c7-40df-b1f0-81e566255d21.png\">\r\n\r\nThe checkpoint state cache shows that we have no more than 3 states per epoch\r\n\r\n<img width=\"791\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2021-10-01 at 17 36 47\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10568965/135606603-3075b861-5b39-493a-b0f5-5949a050191a.png\">\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\n1. There are 1 or 2 redundant epoch transitions per epoch as we can simply get it from the cache\r\n2. Investigate why we have up to 3 epoch transitions per epoch? Ideally most of the time we should have exactly 1 epoch transition per epoch.\r\n\r\nAt least when getting attester duties, we may not need to rotate to the current epoch (most of the time) thanks to the `nextEpochShuffling` cache https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/96ca4d319b386f1c448defe236eba7b7370b2cbe/packages/lodestar/src/api/impl/validator/index.ts#L283\r\n\r\n",
